href="http://www.seattle.gov/sdci/codes/codes-we-enforce-(a-z)/energy-code" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">2015 Seattle Energy Code</a> [SEC], now is a good time to prepare yourself. Working under what’s considered one of the most stringent commercial energy codes in the United States, A/E/C professionals are now better informed on the challenges, the nuances, and the best ways to navigate the requirements to suit a project owner’s best interests.</p><p>Launched on July 1, 2017, and fully implemented on January 1, 2018 <a
href="../blog/2015-seattle-energy-code-lets-adapt.html#section1">[1]</a> the new code might seem harsh and some of the changes have an initial shock factor, but it doesn’t have to be that way. The more we learn about it, work with it, and educate others, human nature will do its job and we’ll do what we do best: adapt.</p></div><div
class="type-defaults"><div
class="my-8 type-defaults text-sm text-gray-600">
